Here is a TekAutomate Steps UI flow to connect to your MSO4/5/6 Series oscilloscope, take a screenshot, and save it as "capture.png". The flow also disconnects at the end.

```json
{
  "steps": [
    {
      "type": "connect",
      "label": "Connect to Oscilloscope",
      "params": {
        "instrumentIds": [],
        "printIdn": true
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "save_screenshot",
      "label": "Save Screenshot as capture.png",
      "params": {
        "filename": "capture.png",
        "scopeType": "modern",
        "method": "pc_transfer"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "disconnect",
      "label": "Disconnect from Oscilloscope",
      "params": {
        "instrumentIds": []
      }
    }
  ]
}
```

You can import this flow into TekAutomate and run it as-is. If you want to change the filename, just edit the "filename" field in the save_screenshot step.

